messages.content: I'm trying to generate zkProgram proof with o1js version 0.13.1 (doing protikit h/w) and it takes up to 11 minutes, whereas on newer versions of o1js takes ~20 sec. Is it related to less optimized processes in earlier versions of o1js?
@maht0rz @rpanic
how are you generating the proofs? 11 Minutes seems like a lot, is compiling also part of that 11 minutes?
Compiling takes 25 sec
I have 15 constraints
how about upgrading to latest o1js then 😄
you are putting out updates faster than we can upgrade 😄
ah I see, didn't realize protokit requires a specific version
after semver we shouldn't be anymore
but so far - yes
nice
there were always quite a few breaking changes so far ^^
Are you using ZkProgram? Or how are you generating the proofs?
Yes, zkProgram
Hmm 🤔
We should be upgrading to o1js 1.0 in a week or two
just fyi proof generation speed is also dependant on nodejs version, newer nodejs handles wasm threads better
Am I the only one who encounter this issue? Anybody else has the same problem, it's kind of suspicious
have you tried newer node version?
Of course I hadn't done it then😅  But now I did and yes it works - compilation + generation takes 25 takes in total. I did not expect such boost
@maht0rz Thanks
v22 works perfectly
